Introduction¶

Dataset Description¶

This data contains three data sets of 186 countries in three main indicators :-

1) population
2) life exectancy
3) income per person

and this data is represnted from year 1800 to year 2050.

Question(s) for Analysis¶

•Is average population of all countries increase by years in past 100 years ?
•Is expected that population will increase in following years ?
•Is average income per person of all countries increase by years in past 100 years ?
•Is expected that income per person will increase in following years ?
•Is average life expectancy of all countries increase by years in past 100 years ?
•Is expected that life expectancy will increase in following years ?
•What is the relationship between income indicator and population and life expectancy indicators ?

Data Cleaning¶

So as we have seen above we don't have same rows, columns and data types and we have also nan values all those need to be fixed

First removing all excess columns

In [98]:
def column_equalizer (x,y):
    for column in y.columns:
        if column not in x.columns:
            y.drop(column,axis=1,inplace=True)
column_equalizer (df_income,df_life)  
column_equalizer (df_income,df_population)

After further investagation,it has been found that some elements in income dataframe and population dataframe have letters that represent a value which are:-

• k equals to 1000
• M equals to 1000000
• B equals to 1000000000

so in order to fix column types we need to change every letter to its value

if column names in income dataframe equals to column names in population dataframe, we only need one list of column names to follow

In [112]:
(df_income.columns==df_population.columns).all()
Out[112]:
True
In [113]:
l=list(df_income.columns[1:])
for v in l:
    df_income[v]=df_income[v].apply(lambda x: (float(x.split('k')[0]))*1000 if ('k' in str(x)) else float(x) )
    df_population[v]=df_population[v].apply(lambda x: (float(x.split('k')[0]))*1000 if ('k' in str(x)) else((float(x.split('M')[0]))*1000000 if ('M' in str(x)) else((float(x.split('B')[0]))*1000000000 if('B' in str(x)) else float(x))))

Conclusions¶

we have data set of 186 countries with main three indicators income per person, total population, life expectancy.After cleaning the data and making some statistics we have found that:-
• Average income per person of all 186 countries has increased from less than 2,500 in year 1800 to more than 20,000 in year 2022 and its expected to increase to more than 37,000 until year 2050.
• Average total population of all 186 countries has increased from less than 1 billion people in year 1800 to 4.5 billion people approximately in year 2022 and its expected to increase to more than 5 billion people until year 2050.
• Average life expectancy of all 186 countries has increased from less than 40 years in year 1800 to 78 years approximately in year 2022 its expected to increase to 80 years approximately until year 2050.
•There's a positive relationship between income per person and total population which means when a person have more money earning, his ability in making a family increases which finally increases population.
•There's a positive relationship between income per person and life expectancy which means when a person have more money earning, his ability to take care of himself increase which in order increases his life expectancy which finally increases population.

limitation¶

there were some countries that didn't have any values so I had to remove them from income dataframe and population dataframe,which may effect the results and produce inacurate statistics.
